						               													<description>Hilarious party game with just the right mix of creativity and creation.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Basic Rules&amp;#10;1. To start the game, each player draws a Challenge Card.&amp;#10;2. One randomly chosen player is elected Reader and pulls a Topic Card. The Reader picks a topic&amp;#10;of their choosing from the Topic Card and reads it aloud.&amp;#10;3. All of the other players answer the question on separate pieces of scratch paper abiding by their&amp;#10;Challenge Card and passes it face down to the Reader.&amp;#10;4. While answers are submitted, the Reader should check handwriting so answers have full effect&amp;#10;when read aloud.&amp;#10;5. The Reader shuffles all of the answers and shares each answer with the group, pausing in between&amp;#10;reading each one. The answer with the most laughs wins a point.&amp;#10;6. After the round, a new player becomes the Reader and everyone re&amp;shy;draws a Challenge Card.&amp;#10;7. The player who reaches 10 points first wins. You can alter the win condition to your game&amp;#10;environment.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Topic Cards:&amp;#10;Words...&amp;#10;Creatively define the word given, but don&amp;rsquo;t worry about coming anywhere close to the real definition!&amp;#10;Just give it whatever meaning strikes you.&amp;#10;Famous People...&amp;#10;Tell us what He or She is famous for...your version anyway. Create an elaborate back story to the&amp;#10;person or tell us a creative tale involving this person.&amp;#10;Movie Titles...&amp;#10;Come up with a terribly clever plot line for the film listed. Is it a documentary? Maybe a hushed noir&amp;#10;film of yesteryear?&amp;#10;Laws...&amp;#10;Fill in the blanks to complete these laws. Your answer can be as long or as short as necessary to&amp;#10;get your point across.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
